@NickElixir unfortunately the folder structure is required right now when using the CLI. If you call the functions directly (e.g. `from label_maker.label import make_labels`) you can specify exact file paths.

It also looks like you will run into some issues with the OSM filters. The format `["has", "tag"]` only checks for the existence of a tag, not for any of its values. So this is suitable for things like `["has", "building"]` or `["has", "highway"]` but not much else. To match a specific tag and value combination, I'd recommend the `==` operator. Here is an example for matching [trees](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tag:natural=tree): `["==", "natural", "tree"]`

Let me know if that all works
